title: Unemployment rate in Fiji 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, containing a total of 21 data points.
In general Unemployment rate has stayed the same over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 4.55 was reached at Year 2015
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 3.62 was reported at Year 2008
